{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1800,"text":"I'm a journalist,"},{"time":3071,"text":"and I'm an immigrant."},{"time":5034,"text":"And these two conditions define me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":8288,"text":"I was born in Mexico,"},{"time":9730,"text":"but I've spent more than half my life\nreporting in the United States,"},{"time":13480,"text":"a country which was itself\ncreated by immigrants."},{"time":16488,"text":"As a reporter"},{"time":19422,"text":"and as a foreigner,"},{"time":21148,"text":"I've learned that neutrality,"},{"time":24319,"text":"silence"},{"time":26024,"text":"and fear aren't the best options --"},{"time":28930,"text":"not in journalism, nor in life."},{"time":31158,"text":"Neutrality"},{"time":33226,"text":"is often an excuse that we journalists use"},{"time":36456,"text":"to hide from our true responsibility."},{"time":39789,"text":"What is that responsibility?"},{"time":42300,"text":"It is to question"},{"time":44232,"text":"and to challenge"},{"time":45769,"text":"those in positions of power."},{"time":47150,"text":"That's what journalism is for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48633,"text":"That's the beauty of journalism:"},{"time":50432,"text":"to question and challenge the powerful."},{"time":53581,"text":"Of course, we have the obligation\nto report reality as it is,"},{"time":57042,"text":"not how we would like it to be."},{"time":58804,"text":"In that sense, I agree\nwith the principle of objectivity:"},{"time":62284,"text":"if a house is blue, I say that it's blue."},{"time":64766,"text":"If there are a million unemployed people,\nI say there are a million."},{"time":68018,"text":"But neutrality"},{"time":69322,"text":"won't necessarily lead me to the truth."},{"time":73201,"text":"Even if I'm unequivocally scrupulous,"},{"time":76764,"text":"and I present both sides of a news item --"},{"time":81108,"text":"the Democratic and the Republican,"},{"time":83243,"text":"the liberal and the conservative,"},{"time":84904,"text":"the government's and the opposition's --"},{"time":86877,"text":"in the end, I have no guarantee,"},{"time":89360,"text":"nor are any of us guaranteed\nthat we'll know what's true"},{"time":92575,"text":"and what's not true."},{"time":94007,"text":"Life is much more complicated,"},{"time":95932,"text":"and I believe journalism should reflect\nthat very complexity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101702,"text":"To be clear: I refuse"},{"time":105334,"text":"to be a tape recorder."},{"time":106700,"text":"I didn't become a journalist\nto be a tape recorder."},{"time":109133,"text":"I know what you're going to say:\nno one uses tape recorders nowadays."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112465,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":113556,"text":"In that case, I refuse\nto take out my cell phone"},{"time":117370,"text":"and hit the record button"},{"time":119823,"text":"and point it in front of me\nas if I were at a concert,"},{"time":122477,"text":"like a fan at a concert."},{"time":124526,"text":"That is not true journalism."},{"time":127120,"text":"Contrary to what many people think,"},{"time":129524,"text":"journalists are making\nvalue judgments all the time,"},{"time":134097,"text":"ethical and moral judgments."},{"time":135970,"text":"And we're always making decisions\nthat are exceedingly personal"},{"time":141822,"text":"and extraordinarily subjective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144011,"text":"For example:"},{"time":145977,"text":"What happens if you're called\nto cover a dictatorship,"},{"time":148580,"text":"like Augusto Pinochet's regime in Chile"},{"time":150669,"text":"or Fidel Castro's in Cuba?"},{"time":153513,"text":"Are you going to report only what\nthe general and commander want,"},{"time":157286,"text":"or will you confront them?"},{"time":159177,"text":"What happens if you find out\nthat in your country"},{"time":163099,"text":"or in the country next door,"},{"time":164941,"text":"students are disappearing"},{"time":167977,"text":"and hidden graves are appearing,"},{"time":170002,"text":"or that millions of dollars\nare disappearing from the budget"},{"time":172994,"text":"and that ex-presidents are magically\nnow multimillionaires?"},{"time":177428,"text":"Will you report only the official version?"},{"time":179501,"text":"Or what happens"},{"time":181625,"text":"if you're assigned to cover"},{"time":183946,"text":"the presidential elections\nof the primary superpower,"},{"time":188993,"text":"and one of the candidates makes\ncomments that are racist,"},{"time":194577,"text":"sexist"},{"time":196244,"text":"and xenophobic?"},{"time":199184,"text":"That happened to me."},{"time":201278,"text":"And I want to tell you what I did,"},{"time":203178,"text":"but first, let me explain\nwhere I'm coming from,"},{"time":205770,"text":"so you can understand my reaction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210690,"text":"I grew up in Mexico City,\nthe oldest of five brothers,"},{"time":213598,"text":"and our family simply couldn't afford\nto pay for all of our college tuition."},{"time":218294,"text":"So I studied in the morning,\nand worked in the afternoon."},{"time":221732,"text":"Eventually,"},{"time":224018,"text":"I got the job I had always wanted:"},{"time":227155,"text":"television reporter."},{"time":228504,"text":"It was a big opportunity."},{"time":230228,"text":"But as I was working on\nmy third story, I ended up"},{"time":233825,"text":"criticizing the president,"},{"time":235856,"text":"and questioning the lack\nof democracy in Mexico."},{"time":239334,"text":"In Mexico, from 1929 to 2000,\nelections were always rigged;"},{"time":244229,"text":"the incumbent president\nwould hand-pick his successor."},{"time":248397,"text":"That's not true democracy."},{"time":251783,"text":"To me it seemed like a brilliant idea\nto expose the president,"},{"time":254812,"text":"but to my boss --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":256063,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":257920,"text":"My boss didn't think\nit was such a great idea."},{"time":260150,"text":"At that time, the presidential office,\nLos Pinos, had issued a direct censor"},{"time":263901,"text":"against the media."},{"time":265399,"text":"My boss, who, aside from being in charge\nof the show I worked for,"},{"time":269185,"text":"was also in charge of a soccer team."},{"time":273064,"text":"I always suspected that he was more\ninterested in goals"},{"time":275896,"text":"than in the news."},{"time":277298,"text":"He censored my report."},{"time":279130,"text":"He asked me to change it, I said no,"},{"time":281275,"text":"so he put another journalist on the story"},{"time":284235,"text":"to write what I was supposed to say."},{"time":287989,"text":"I did not want to be\na censored journalist."},{"time":291578,"text":"I don't know where I found the strength,"},{"time":293857,"text":"but I wrote my letter of resignation."},{"time":296152,"text":"And so at 24 years of age -- just 24 --"},{"time":300482,"text":"I made the most difficult and most\ntranscendental decision of my life."},{"time":303878,"text":"Not only did I resign from television,"},{"time":306055,"text":"but I had also decided\nto leave my country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309508,"text":"I sold my car, a beat-up\nlittle red Volkswagen,"},{"time":313249,"text":"came up with some money"},{"time":315064,"text":"and said goodbye to my family,"},{"time":316862,"text":"to my friends,"},{"time":318085,"text":"to my streets,"},{"time":319465,"text":"to my favorite haunts -- to my tacos --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":321578,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":322879,"text":"and I bought a one-way ticket"},{"time":325100,"text":"to Los Angeles, California."},{"time":327303,"text":"And so I became"},{"time":329232,"text":"one of the 250 million immigrants\nthat exist in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334082,"text":"Ask any immigrant"},{"time":335922,"text":"about the first day they arrived\nin their new country,"},{"time":338492,"text":"and you'll find that they remember\nabsolutely everything,"},{"time":341243,"text":"like it was a movie with background music."},{"time":343325,"text":"In my case, I arrived in Los Angeles,\nthe sun was setting,"},{"time":347341,"text":"and everything I owned --"},{"time":349106,"text":"a guitar, a suitcase and some documents --"},{"time":351738,"text":"I could carry all of it"},{"time":354139,"text":"with my two hands."},{"time":355322,"text":"That feeling of absolute freedom,"},{"time":358288,"text":"I haven't experienced since."},{"time":360093,"text":"And I survived with what little I had."},{"time":363530,"text":"I obtained a student visa; I was studying."},{"time":368156,"text":"I ate a lot of lettuce and bread,\nbecause that's all I had."},{"time":371135,"text":"Finally, in 1984,"},{"time":374188,"text":"I landed my first job as a TV reporter\nin the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378435,"text":"And the first thing I noticed\nwas that in the US,"},{"time":382506,"text":"my colleagues criticized --\nand mercilessly --"},{"time":384713,"text":"then president Ronald Reagan,"},{"time":386222,"text":"and absolutely nothing happened;\nno one censored them."},{"time":389134,"text":"And I thought:"},{"time":390846,"text":"I love this country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392368,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":395326,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":398722,"text":"And that's how it's been"},{"time":400889,"text":"for more than 30 years:"},{"time":403361,"text":"reporting with total freedom,"},{"time":405315,"text":"and being treated as an equal\ndespite being an immigrant --"},{"time":408245,"text":"until, without warning,"},{"time":409919,"text":"I was assigned to cover the recent\nUS presidential election."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416536,"text":"On June 16, 2015,"},{"time":420328,"text":"a candidate who would eventually become\nthe president of the United States"},{"time":424445,"text":"said that Mexican immigrants"},{"time":428448,"text":"were criminals,"},{"time":431276,"text":"drug traffickers"},{"time":433108,"text":"and rapists."},{"time":434292,"text":"And I knew"},{"time":436305,"text":"that he was lying."},{"time":437481,"text":"I knew he was wrong\nfor one very simple reason:"},{"time":440346,"text":"I'm a Mexican immigrant."},{"time":442457,"text":"And we're not like that."},{"time":443840,"text":"So I did what any other reporter\nwould have done:"},{"time":448113,"text":"I wrote him a letter by hand"},{"time":451173,"text":"requesting an interview,"},{"time":452968,"text":"and I sent it to his Tower in New York."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455370,"text":"The next day"},{"time":457285,"text":"I was at work,"},{"time":458508,"text":"and I suddenly began to receive\nhundreds of calls and texts"},{"time":462105,"text":"on my cell phone,"},{"time":463618,"text":"some more insulting than others."},{"time":465184,"text":"I didn't know what was happening\nuntil my friend came into my office"},{"time":468705,"text":"and said, \"They published\nyour cell number online.\""},{"time":473608,"text":"They actually did that."},{"time":475944,"text":"Here's the letter they sent"},{"time":479342,"text":"where they gave out my number."},{"time":481980,"text":"Don't bother writing it down, OK?\nI already changed it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484666,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":486202,"text":"But I learned two things."},{"time":487834,"text":"The first one is that you should\nnever, never, ever"},{"time":492309,"text":"give your cell number to Donald Trump."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495198,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":498026,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":501426,"text":"The second lesson was that\nI needed to stop being neutral"},{"time":505787,"text":"at that point."},{"time":506972,"text":"From then on, my mission\nas a journalist changed."},{"time":509677,"text":"I would confront the candidate"},{"time":512323,"text":"and show that he was wrong,"},{"time":513996,"text":"that what he said about immigrants\nin the US was not true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517370,"text":"Let me give you some figures."},{"time":518812,"text":"Ninety-seven percent of all undocumented\npeople in the United States"},{"time":523006,"text":"are good people."},{"time":524338,"text":"Less than three percent\nhave committed a serious crime,"},{"time":527215,"text":"or \"felony,\" as they say in English."},{"time":528971,"text":"In comparison, six percent of US citizens\nhave committed a serious crime."},{"time":533565,"text":"The conclusion is that undocumented\nimmigrants behave much better"},{"time":539427,"text":"than US citizens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540964,"text":"Based on that data, I made a plan."},{"time":543832,"text":"Eight weeks after they published\nmy cell number,"},{"time":548054,"text":"I obtained a press pass\nfor a press conference"},{"time":550793,"text":"for the candidate\ngaining momentum in the polls."},{"time":554242,"text":"I decided to confront him"},{"time":556541,"text":"in person."},{"time":558520,"text":"But ..."},{"time":560372,"text":"things didn't turn out exactly\nas I had planned; watch:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":565529,"text":"[Donald Trump Press Conference\nDubuque, Iowa]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":570889,"text":"(Video) Jorge Ramos: Mr. Trump,\nI have a question about immigration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574113,"text":"Donald Trump: Who's next? Yes, please."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576003,"text":"JR: Your immigration plan\nis full of empty promises."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578464,"text":"DT: Excuse me, you weren't called.\nSit down. Sit down!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":581021,"text":"JR: I'm a reporter; as an immigrant\nand as a US citizen,"},{"time":583723,"text":"I have the right to ask a question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585422,"text":"DT: No you don't.\nJR: I have the right to ask --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":587729,"text":"DT: Go back to Univision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588946,"text":"JR: This is the question:"},{"time":590166,"text":"You cannot deport 11 million people."},{"time":593008,"text":"You cannot build a 1900-mile wall."},{"time":596195,"text":"You cannot deny citizenship\nto children in this country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599904,"text":"DT: Sit down.\nJR: And with those ideas --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":601869,"text":"DT: You weren't called."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603045,"text":"JR: I'm a reporter and I have --\nDon't touch me, sir."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606093,"text":"Guard 1: Please don't disrupt.\nYou're being disruptive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":608715,"text":"JR: I have the right to ask a question.\nG1: Yes, in order. In turn, sir."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612297,"text":"Guard 2: Do you have\nyour media credential?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":614342,"text":"JR: I have the right --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":615519,"text":"G2: Where? Let me see.\nJR: It's over there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617552,"text":"Man: Whoever's coming out, stay out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619306,"text":"G2: You've just got to wait your turn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621172,"text":"Man: You're very rude. It's not about you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623223,"text":"JR: It's not about you --\nMan: Get out of my country!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":625775,"text":"Man: It's not about you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626968,"text":"JR: I'm a US citizen, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628244,"text":"Man: Well ...whatever.\nNo, Univision. It's not about you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630945,"text":"JR: It's not about you.\nIt's about the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636275,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":647361,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":650951,"text":"Whenever I see that video,"},{"time":652810,"text":"the first thing I always\nthink is that hate"},{"time":656124,"text":"is contagious."},{"time":657417,"text":"If you notice, after the candidate says,\n\"Go back to Univision\" -- that's code;"},{"time":661731,"text":"what he's telling me\nis, \"Get out of here.\""},{"time":663950,"text":"One member of his entourage,\nas if he had been given permission, said,"},{"time":667811,"text":"\"Get out of my country,\""},{"time":670230,"text":"not knowing that I'm also a US citizen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675083,"text":"After watching this video many times,"},{"time":677620,"text":"I also think that in order\nto break free from neutrality --"},{"time":680638,"text":"and for it to be a true break --"},{"time":682211,"text":"one has to lose their fear,"},{"time":684407,"text":"and then learn how to say, \"No;"},{"time":686636,"text":"I'm not going to be quiet."},{"time":688748,"text":"I'm not going to sit down."},{"time":691079,"text":"And I'm not going to leave.\""},{"time":692975,"text":"The word \"no\" --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":694484,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":699113,"text":"\"no\" is the most powerful word\nthat exists in any language,"},{"time":703009,"text":"and it always precedes\nany important change in our lives."},{"time":706305,"text":"And I think there's enormous dignity"},{"time":708522,"text":"and it generates a great deal of respect"},{"time":710476,"text":"to be able to step back"},{"time":712029,"text":"and to push back and say,"},{"time":714189,"text":"\"No.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":715379,"text":"Elie Wiesel -- Holocaust survivor,"},{"time":717985,"text":"Nobel Peace Prize recipient"},{"time":719343,"text":"and who, unfortunately,\nwe lost very recently --"},{"time":722181,"text":"said some very wise words:"},{"time":724532,"text":"\"We must take a side."},{"time":726956,"text":"Neutrality helps only the oppressor,"},{"time":729496,"text":"never the victim.\""},{"time":730671,"text":"And he's completely right."},{"time":731940,"text":"We journalists are obligated\nto take sides in certain circumstances;"},{"time":735806,"text":"in cases of racism,"},{"time":737656,"text":"discrimination,"},{"time":739426,"text":"corruption,"},{"time":740821,"text":"lying to the public,"},{"time":742329,"text":"dictatorships and human rights,"},{"time":744265,"text":"we need to set aside\nneutrality and indifference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747796,"text":"Spanish has a great word"},{"time":750320,"text":"to describe the stance\nthat journalists should take."},{"time":754383,"text":"The word is \n\"contrapoder [anti-establishment].\""},{"time":756645,"text":"Basically, we journalists\nshould be on the opposite side"},{"time":760566,"text":"from those in power."},{"time":762182,"text":"But if you're in bed with politicians,"},{"time":764780,"text":"if you go to the baptism or wedding\nof the governor's son"},{"time":767501,"text":"or if you want to be\nthe president's buddy,"},{"time":769574,"text":"how are you going to criticize them?"},{"time":771439,"text":"When I'm assigned to interview\na powerful or influential person,"},{"time":774752,"text":"I always keep two things in mind:"},{"time":776525,"text":"if I don't ask this difficult\nand uncomfortable question,"},{"time":779293,"text":"no one else is going to;"},{"time":781898,"text":"and that I'm never going to see\nthis person again."},{"time":784865,"text":"So I'm not looking to make\na good impression"},{"time":788952,"text":"or to forge a connection."},{"time":790280,"text":"In the end, if I have to choose\nbetween being the president's friend"},{"time":793547,"text":"or enemy,"},{"time":794729,"text":"I always prefer to be their enemy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799181,"text":"In closing:"},{"time":801340,"text":"I know this is a difficult time\nto be an immigrant and a journalist,"},{"time":806258,"text":"but now more than ever,"},{"time":808160,"text":"we need journalists who are prepared,"},{"time":811345,"text":"at any given moment,"},{"time":812940,"text":"to set neutrality aside."},{"time":815357,"text":"Personally, I feel like\nI've been preparing for this moment"},{"time":818219,"text":"my whole life."},{"time":819397,"text":"When they censored me when I was 24,"},{"time":821707,"text":"I learned that neutrality, fear\nand silence often make you an accomplice"},{"time":828401,"text":"in crime, abuse"},{"time":830847,"text":"and injustice."},{"time":832418,"text":"And being an accomplice to power"},{"time":834467,"text":"is never good journalism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":837574,"text":"Now, at 59 years old,"},{"time":840268,"text":"I only hope to have a tiny bit"},{"time":843090,"text":"of the courage and mental\nclarity I had at 24,"},{"time":847121,"text":"and that way, never again"},{"time":849465,"text":"remain quiet."},{"time":850862,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852154,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":854817,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856024,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}